	<ModId Value="128269" />
	<!--Name of the mod to display to players-->
	<DisplayName Value="Zone Tools" />
	<!--Short description of the mod-->
	<ShortDescription Value="Change zoning on any side of a road; for new roads or updating existing roads." />
	<!--Long description of the mod. Single line or multi line. Supports minimal markdown subset-->
	<LongDescription>### Zone Tools

Direct control over road zoning for **new roads** and **existing roads**.

- Movable floating panel (drag from title bar).
- Optional **Contour** button synced with vanilla **topography**
- This is the older mod with a movable panel. If you prefer icons in a static game panel, try new Easy Zoning mod (complete redesign).

### New roads

- Open zone panel by clicking the button (top-left) or hotkey (default Shift+X)
- Pre-select: both, left, right, or none (move the panel where you like).
- Draw a new road (note: road draw direction influences vanilla side).

### Update Existing Roads (UER):

- Open zoning panel (top-left button or hotkey)
- Enable the **Update Roads** button (recycle icon). Click again to turn off.
- Select the side you want (both, left, right, none buttons).
- Left click on roads to update zoning (supports click-and-drag to update many roads).
- Left mouse applies the zone change. Select different icons to change.
- Right mouse click will also cycle the 4-zone options.

Power Trick: if you have existing roads and do not want a new road intersecting it to alter zoning, pick **None**, then draw the new road. 
Your existing road should keep zoning facing the same original direction you set.

## Options Menu

- ✅ Protect occupied cells (buildings) 
- ✅ Protect zoned-but-empty cells
- ✅ Contour terrain lines button
- ✅ Change keybind shortcut (Options menu)
- ✅ Panel style option: **Glass** transparent or **Vanilla gray**

### Support and Feedback

- if the mod helped, give it a Like, it's free + easy :)
- Feedback to Github link or discord, or forum.

### Tech notes

- Does not use Harmony patches; uses CS2 native systems (more compatible with the game and other mods).
- Safe to remove any time.  Roads keep their zoning edits so buildings don't get deleted.
- Should work with Platter mod.
- Contour button will not do anything if Crosswalk, or Wide Sidewalk, etc., is selected as that is not allowed in vanilla.
Main goal of the contour button is to show terrain lines while updating Existing roads; as a bonus, it happens to also work in other tool modes.
Contour enables what is safe to do without overriding the game's vanilla system (e.g avoids Harmony patch).
- Glass panel does not use blur (heavier work); uses a lighter plain transparent + tint (works in normal + Legacy mode).

### 11 Languages

- English, Français French, Deutsch German, Español Spanish, Italiano Italian
- 한국어 Korean, 日本語 Japanese, 简体中文 Simplified Chinese
- 繁體中文 Traditional Chinese, Português Brasil, Polski Polish

### Credits

   - River-mochi author
    - thanks to zeeshanabid94 for original ZoningToolKit (retired)
- yenyang for technical advisory
- =Noel= for Chinese locale review

</LongDescription>
